# Applications under test in the eval-desktop container.
# One apt package per line. Blank lines and # comments are ignored.
# Goal: surface variety across a11y backends (AT-SPI adapters differ per toolkit),
# not completeness. Expand based on which regressions we actually catch.

# GTK3 — AT-SPI backend, baseline for Linux accessibility probes
gedit

# LibreOffice Calc — mixed toolkit (VCL + AT-SPI bridge), stresses table/grid grounding
libreoffice-calc

# Qt5/Qt6 reference app — exercises QAccessible bridge, different from GTK
# kcalc is lighter than qtcreator (~15MB vs ~500MB) and pulls enough Qt runtime
# to cover the Qt accessibility surface we care about.
kcalc

# Xterm — minimal X client, useful as a "does windowing work at all" smoke target
xterm
